 the critical lens through which to effect positive change. This, they argue, will need to draw on a co-production model maintained through a well-resourced special purpose organisation set up to mobilise and resource planning intermediaries whose role it is to activate, support and educate those without the resources to secure such advocacy themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic assistance, DomesticzGreat Britain. 0aEconomic development projectsxPlanning. 0aNeoliberalism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aStreet, Emma, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831111966640 cprintz978144734139040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447341406?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447341406423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447341406/original  a978-3-11-119666-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles